(preamble
  :dialect "sakura"
  :audience "engineer"
  :training-eligible #f
  :confidentiality "internal"
  :prose "Canonical engineering doc #7 of the sealed Motoi Scheme 1.0 doc-set. Audience: SRE; any engineer touching a wire-call module; any future archaeologist trying to understand which capability calls which upstream; any auditor reviewing the vendor-naming firewall. Voice: HelloSurface gold standard — dry, structured, data-rich, file:line-anchored. The integration boundary is the one place vendor names ARE permitted in the codebase (CLAUDE.md 2026-06-22 lock); this doc names every vendor explicitly. Corresponding cart-side, Scheme-side, and operator-side surfaces never name them. Author: Alfred Robins / Claude Code (PM lane) 2026-06-30. Last drift pass covers-through 2026-07-11.")

(chapter :number 1
         :title "§0 — What integration means at Lacuna"
         :section "0"
         :dialect "sakura"
         :audience "engineer"
         :training-eligible #f
         :confidentiality "internal"
         :provenance ((:source-path "/Users/alfred/code/sakura-scheme/docs/engineering/LACUNA-INTEGRATION-1.0.ENG.md") (:source-anchor "§0"))
         :prose "Two-axis design. Axis 1 — capability verbs (cart-facing): the cart corpus calls capability-shape verb names (etsy/listings, model/workhorse, web/search, cortex/recall, mail/dispatch). These are the names cart authors (human and LLM) write. A capability verb names WHAT WORK HAPPENS without committing to who does it. The cart corpus does not know which upstream services Lacuna talks to; if vendor identifiers leak in, they bake into the on-device savant's weights (CLAUDE.md 2026-06-22 lock). Axis 2 — wire-call modules (vendor-facing): behind each capability verb is exactly one Python module that owns the HTTP boundary to a named upstream. etsy/listings resolves to curator_api.stores.etsy.EtsyClient.list_listings(...). One module, one boundary, one allowed location for the vendor name.

Vendor-naming firewall. Per CLAUDE.md 2026-06-22 lock, 14 tokens are banned EVERYWHERE except the literal wire-call HTTP method: Claude, Anthropic, Sonnet, Opus, Qwen, Llama, Mistral, Gemini, Perplexity, Firecrawl, DeepSeek, Vertex, OpenAI, GPT. Banned in operator-facing UI copy, cart doc-blocks, training corpus, system prompts, internal backend modules/route names/function names/log messages, backend Python vendor-selection code. Permitted only in the wire-call modules (batch_anthropic.py, batch_gemini.py, cache_gemini.py, direct_clients.py, _llm.py at :438, :674-675, :959), this document, and OSS attribution files. Enforcement: scripts/audit_carts.py:108-118 and scripts/cart_lint.py:139-152 enforce the ban on the cart corpus; a vendor-name leak in a cart is a hard fail. Marketplace names STAY visible (Etsy, eBay, Shopify, Meta, Instagram, Printify, Stripe, Google Shopping/Merchant) — these are product surfaces operators sell on. Only LLM/scrape/vision reasoning vendors are firewalled.

Integration contract — four invariants. (1) Single boundary: each vendor has exactly one Python module owning its HTTP surface. (2) Honest-null on missing credential: {ok: False, error: service-not-yet-wired, reason: <vendor>-not-connected} instead of raising. (3) Mock-first: each public function accepts optional transport: httpx.BaseTransport for httpx.MockTransport injection; W4 spec mandates this; batch_anthropic.py:31-34, etsy/client.py:14-17, shopify/client.py:71 comply. (4) Operator-commit gate on every write: any verb that mutates upstream state requires operator_commit: true on ctx, checked defensively at the wire-call module boundary; etsy/client.py:50-55, shopify/client.py:38-43, meta/dispatcher.py:79-82, batch_anthropic.py:90-101.

Document scope. Covers vendors shipping production wire-calls as of 2026-06-30. Perplexity, Pinterest, Reddit, Spotify are deliberately not integrated per CLAUDE.md 'Out-of-scope vendors (W01 wire lock, 2026-06-14)'; lint blocks any cart referencing their namespaces. Vendor wire-calls listed as 'status: NOT WIRED' exist in shops/router descriptors but lack HTTP-route layer; corresponding carts return service-not-yet-wired.")

(chapter :number 2
         :title "§1 — Verb → backing map; wired verb set; unwired surface"
         :section "1"
         :dialect "sakura"
         :audience "engineer"
         :training-eligible #f
         :confidentiality "internal"
         :provenance ((:source-path "/Users/alfred/code/sakura-scheme/docs/engineering/LACUNA-INTEGRATION-1.0.ENG.md") (:source-anchor "§1"))
         :prose "The verb registry is the single source of truth for which capabilities exist. The HTTP route module (curator-api/curator_api/routes/verb_backings.py) is the single source of truth for which capabilities have a wire-call backing. The intersection is the set of carts that actually run today.

Wired-verb set: 83 verbs, 7 waves. Source: scripts/build_cart_index.mjs:324 (WIRED_VERBS set). Grew from 62 to 83 between the 2026-06-30 draft and HEAD d4f5a8a4. Waves 1-6 (2026-06-15 through 2026-06-30) added the base set; Wave 7B (2026-06-29) added 8 admin-only routes for batch/cache (model/batch-anthropic-{submit,status,retrieve}, model/batch-gemini-{submit,status,retrieve}, model/cache-gemini-{create,delete}) and 2 SRE admin endpoints (/api/admin/cost/summary, /api/admin/cost/dashboard-widget). Batch/cache verbs are admin-only route handlers and are not members of the cart-facing WIRED_VERBS set. Wave 7 (2026-07 honest-null wiring burndown) added remaining 21 verbs lifting the set to 83. Three groups: marketplace read-siblings (2026-07-03 P1/HN-3) — etsy/messages, etsy/sections, ebay/feedback, shopify/customers, ebay/fees, ebay/orders, etsy/list-*, etsy/listing-detail, etsy/order-detail, shopify/listings; web/documents (2026-07-03 P2/HN-1) — documents/parse, web/extract-schema, web/monitor; vision/Cortex read family — vision/describe, vision/embed, vision/ocr, cortex/event, cortex/fetch, cortex/query, cortex/read, cortex/read-memory. CI sync-guard pins agreement: wiredVerbsSync.test.js asserts every WIRED_VERBS member has a route mapping in verbBackings.js (commit d1c77085); adding a verb to one side without the other fails CI.

Verb → wire-call resolution table (representative rows). cortex/recall → verb_backings.py:171 → cortex.memory.CortexStore.list_memos → local. cortex/remember → :214 → cortex.memory.CortexStore.create_memo → local. cortex/forget → :2154 → cortex.expunge. cortex/multi-store-publish → :1346 → cross_marketplace.publish → multi (etsy/ebay/shopify fan-out). loam/operator-state → :284 → _operator_settings.get_settings + loam.shell_chain. model/fast → :360 → _llm.LocalOllamaBackend (degrades to honest-null) → localhost:11434. model/deep-reasoning → :886 → llm_router.router → direct_clients → api.anthropic.com/v1/messages. model/batch-anthropic-* → (W7B) → llm_router.batch_anthropic → api.anthropic.com/v1/messages/batches. model/batch-gemini-* → (W7B) → llm_router.batch_gemini → generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta/.../batchGenerateContent. etsy/listings → :556 → stores.etsy.EtsyClient.list_listings → openapi.etsy.com/v3/application. shopify/products → :720 → stores.shopify.ShopifyClient.list_products → <shop>.myshopify.com/admin/api/2026-01. meta/products → :1215 → stores.meta.MetaClient → graph.facebook.com/v22.0. web/scrape → :774 → firecrawl.tools.scrape → api.firecrawl.dev/v1/scrape. voice/transcribe → :2365 (W6) → voice.transcribe.transcribe → Google Speech-to-Text OR honest-null. Full table in source .md; line-number cites predate Wave-7 growth and need bulk re-verification per living TODO.

Verbs in shops.js but NOT yet wired (top-20 leverage). Counted 2,628 INFRA-WAITING carts as of 2026-06-30, predates P2/HN-1 wave that landed five verbs now marked wired. Leverage verbs: documents/parse (113/69 — WIRED P2/HN-1); model/vision-photo (115/59 — no backing); model/grounded (55/43 — no backing); model/cache-warm (66/37 — no backing); web/extract-schema (77/29 — WIRED P2/HN-1); model/code-execute (60/29); web/monitor (41/29 — WIRED P2/HN-1); image/compose (107/24); vision/describe (60/23 — WIRED); scene/imagine (54/22 — canvas-side only); vision/embed (71/20 — WIRED); stripe/payouts (17 blocked — NOT WIRED); google/merchant-feed (5 — NOT WIRED). Five P2/HN-1 verbs degrade honestly: when upstream dependency unavailable, handler returns ok-degraded with reason, not fabricated result. vision/ocr shares same wave (vision_ocr() at :1694). Remaining unwired surface documented as feature: every infra-waiting cart returns structured service-not-yet-wired envelope.")

(chapter :number 3
         :title "§2.1–§2.4 — Etsy, eBay, Shopify, Printify wire-call modules"
         :section "2.1-2.4"
         :dialect "sakura"
         :audience "engineer"
         :training-eligible #f
         :confidentiality "internal"
         :provenance ((:source-path "/Users/alfred/code/sakura-scheme/docs/engineering/LACUNA-INTEGRATION-1.0.ENG.md") (:source-anchor "§2.1-§2.4"))
         :prose "Etsy (§2.1). Namespace etsy/* (12 verbs wired as of W6). Modules: curator-api/curator_api/stores/etsy.py (OAuth-bound EtsyClient — list_listings, get_listing, list_receipts, list_images, list_conversations, list_reviews, get_shop plus W6 orders/inventory/ledger/reprice extensions); curator-api/curator_api/etsy/client.py:44 (ETSY_API_BASE — Wave-5a wrapper). Upstream: https://openapi.etsy.com/v3/application. Auth: OAuth 2.0 + x-api-key threaded as oauth_token + api_key (etsy/client.py:75-79); either missing yields service-not-yet-wired with etsy-not-connected or etsy-shop-id-missing (etsy/client.py:66-72). Verb table: etsy/listings GET /shops/{shop_id}/listings; etsy/listing GET /listings/{listing_id}; etsy/receipts GET /shops/{shop_id}/receipts; etsy/images GET /listings/{listing_id}/images; etsy/conversations GET /conversations; etsy/reviews GET /listings/{listing_id}/reviews; etsy/shop GET /shops/{shop_id}; etsy/orders (W6) GET /shops/{shop_id}/receipts?was_paid=true; etsy/inventory (W6) GET /listings/{listing_id}/inventory; etsy/ledger (W6) GET /shops/{shop_id}/payment-account/ledger-entries; etsy/reprice (W6) PUT /shops/{shop_id}/listings/{listing_id}/inventory (operator-commit required). Wire discipline in etsy/client.py:82-128 (_wire_get + _wire_write are ONLY two places HTTP methods land; both accept transport injection seam). Rate limit: 10 q/s + 10,000/day per app.

eBay (§2.2). Namespace ebay/* (3 verbs wired). Modules: stores/ebay.py (OAuth-bound EbayClient); ebay/sell.py:26 (W6/Wave-5b wrapper). Upstreams: api.ebay.com/sell/inventory/v1, sell/account/v1, buy/browse/v1. Auth: OAuth 2.0 with refresh tokens; sandbox api.sandbox.ebay.com. Verb table: ebay/listings GET sell/inventory/v1/inventory_item; ebay/sold GET sell/fulfillment/v1/order (paid filter); ebay/update PUT sell/inventory/v1/inventory_item/{sku} (operator-commit required). ~16 additional ebay/* verbs declared but not wired.

Shopify (§2.3). Namespace shopify/* (3 verbs wired). Modules: stores/shopify.py (production); shopify/client.py (Wave-5a dispatcher for Admin GraphQL 2026-01 + REST). Upstream: https://{shop_domain}/admin/api/2026-01 (multi-tenant — each operator's shop owns its own subdomain). API version 2026-01 (shopify/client.py:32); Shopify rolls a new API version every quarter; pin to most recent stable at module load. Auth: OAuth 2.0 shop-scoped, threaded as oauth_token + shop_domain; missing either yields service-not-yet-wired. Verb table: shopify/products POST GraphQL products query; shopify/orders POST GraphQL orders query; shopify/update POST GraphQL productUpdate mutation (operator-commit required). ~28 shopify/* verbs declared but not wired (Functions, Markets, Flow, ReturnReasonDefinition, orderUpdate.phone, Discount Functions, Cart Transform Functions, Validation Functions, X-01 inventory firewall reservation).

Printify (§2.4). Namespace printify/* (1 verb partially wired via stores). Modules: printify/client.py; dispatchers/printify_dispatcher.py (cross-marketplace hook); vendors/printify.py (Bearer-token shape). Upstream: https://api.printify.com/v1. Auth: OAuth 2.0 public-app. Status: printify/products (cross-store publishing fan-out) wired through cross_marketplace module. ~49 other printify/* verbs (printify/orders, printify/designs, printify/blueprints, printify/print-providers) declared but unwired.")

(chapter :number 4
         :title "§2.5–§2.7 — Meta, Instagram, Google (22 modules)"
         :section "2.5-2.7"
         :dialect "sakura"
         :audience "engineer"
         :training-eligible #f
         :confidentiality "internal"
         :provenance ((:source-path "/Users/alfred/code/sakura-scheme/docs/engineering/LACUNA-INTEGRATION-1.0.ENG.md") (:source-anchor "§2.5-§2.7"))
         :prose "Meta (§2.5). Namespace meta/* (3 verbs wired, ~27 declared). Modules: stores/meta.py (production MetaClient); meta/dispatcher.py (Wave-5c seam over MetaClient — lists 27 verbs at :1-50). Upstream: https://graph.facebook.com/v22.0. Auth: OAuth 2.0 with long-lived page tokens; oauth_token + page_id (or business_id) on ctx. Verb table (wired): meta/products GET /{catalog_id}/products; meta/marketplace GET/POST /{page_id}/marketplace_listings; meta/orders (W6) GET /{page_id}/commerce_orders. NOT wired per dispatcher.py:1-31: meta/catalog-product-{create,update,delete}, meta/catalog-batch, meta/catalog-audit, meta/catalog-feed-push, meta/catalog-summary, meta/product-set-{create,list}, meta/shop-stats, meta/shop-refund, meta/page-post, meta/page-roles, meta/page-insights, meta/messenger-send (24h window), meta/messenger-template, meta/marketplace-listing-{create,renew}, meta/marketplace-respond (response-rate budget), meta/lead-form-rows, meta/ads-creative-create, meta/ads-audience-create (lookalike), meta/pixel-events, meta/webhook-subscribe, meta/app-deprecation-watch, meta/business-assets. Rate limit: Meta enforces Business Use Case (BUC) rate limits per operator; dispatcher.py:38-46 consults per-operator RateLimiter; honest rate-limited envelope returned per :73-76.

Instagram (§2.6). Namespace instagram/* (1 verb wired). Module: instagram/dispatcher.py (plus human_agent.py for handoff workflow). Upstream: graph.facebook.com/v22.0/{user_id} and graph.instagram.com. Auth: OAuth via Meta Business. Verb: instagram/post POST /{ig_user_id}/media + /media_publish (operator-commit required). NOT wired: instagram/insights (9 blocked), instagram/comments (5), instagram/container (3), instagram/dm, instagram/stories.

Google (§2.7). Broadest vendor surface. 22 modules under curator-api/curator_api/google/. Active wire-calls: google/places.py → places/near-me (NOT yet wired beyond stub) at places.googleapis.com/v1; google/ga4_data.py + google/ga4_admin.py → analytics/report (wired) at analyticsdata.googleapis.com/v1beta; google/merchant_api.py + google/merchant_center.py → google/merchant-feed, google/merchant-center, google-merchant/* (NOT WIRED) at merchantapi.googleapis.com/products/v1beta; google/gmail.py used by mail/* template paths at gmail.googleapis.com/v1; google/calendar_api.py → cortex/calendar (local) consults for events at calendar.googleapis.com/v3; google/drive.py used by Cortex artifact persistence at www.googleapis.com/drive/v3; google/sheets.py + google/docs.py (no direct cart verb yet); google/document_ai.py → documents/parse-invoice route (W3) at <region>-documentai.googleapis.com; google/vision_web.py → vision/label (partial) at vision.googleapis.com/v1; google/translate.py → translate/text NOT yet wired at translation.googleapis.com/v3; google/natural_language.py → entity/lookup NOT yet wired at language.googleapis.com/v1; google/speech_to_text.py backs voice/transcribe indirect via voice.transcribe at speech.googleapis.com/v1; google/tts.py backs voice/synthesize indirect via voice.synth at texttospeech.googleapis.com/v1; google/geocoding.py → geo/geocode-address NOT wired at maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/geocode/json; google/routes.py → routes/drive-time NOT wired at routes.googleapis.com; google/search_console.py → seo/queries NOT wired at searchconsole.googleapis.com/v1; google/knowledge_graph.py (internal lookups) at kgsearch.googleapis.com/v1/entities:search; google/ads.py → ads/insights route exists but google.ads NOT WIRED at googleads.googleapis.com/v17; google/recaptcha.py (server-side gating) at recaptchaenterprise.googleapis.com/v1; google/vertex_ai.py NOT USED per W7B Vertex-shift abandonment (see §7). Auth: Service-account credentials (JSON key file or workload identity); OAuth 2.0 for end-user Drive/Sheets/Docs/Gmail/Calendar. Per-operator credentials in encrypted Loam state; service-account keys in ~/.curator-secrets/ (mode 0600 per CLAUDE.md). Quota: google/quota.py is centralized quota tracker for Google API daily caps.")

(chapter :number 5
         :title "§2.8–§2.9 — Anthropic + Gemini (direct-vendor LLM paths)"
         :section "2.8-2.9"
         :dialect "sakura"
         :audience "engineer"
         :training-eligible #f
         :confidentiality "internal"
         :provenance ((:source-path "/Users/alfred/code/sakura-scheme/docs/engineering/LACUNA-INTEGRATION-1.0.ENG.md") (:source-anchor "§2.8-§2.9"))
         :prose "Anthropic (§2.8). Capability verbs: model/deep-reasoning, model/workhorse (routed through router); model/batch-anthropic-* (W7B). Modules: _llm.py:438 (URL='https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages', realtime Messages endpoint); llm_router/batch_anthropic.py (batch tier; _API_BASE='https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages/batches' at :61); llm_router/direct_clients.py (realtime direct client); llm_router/router.py (capability router deciding realtime vs batch). Upstreams: Messages (realtime) https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages; Messages Batches https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages/batches. API version header: anthropic-version: 2023-06-01 (batch_anthropic.py:62). Batch beta header: anthropic-beta: message-batches-2024-09-24 (:63). Auth: x-api-key header (:106); key read from ANTHROPIC_API_KEY env var (:79); if unset, is_configured() returns False and routes return honest-null. Models in production routing: model/reasoner (light-purple / Dream) → claude-sonnet-4-5-20251022 (batch_anthropic.py:68 _VERB_TO_MODEL); model/opus (deep-purple / Magic) → claude-opus-4-5-20251022 (:69). Cart corpus calls these via capability verbs; router resolves capability → model. Model strings are vendor identifiers and live only in wire-call modules. Operator-commit gate: every batch SUBMIT requires operator_commit: true on ctx (batch_anthropic.py:39-41, :90-101). Even at 50% batch discount, single submit can fan out to thousands of requests; operator-commit gate stands. Cost: batch tier 50% off realtime per WAVE-7B:10-17; cost ledger records both tiers.

Gemini (§2.9). Capability verbs: model/workhorse / model/fast may route to Gemini in mixed-vendor configurations; model/batch-gemini-* and model/cache-gemini-* (W7B). Modules: _llm.py:674-675 (realtime + streaming generateContent URL templates); llm_router/batch_gemini.py (_API_BASE='https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta' at :52); llm_router/cache_gemini.py (context caching for 75% off cached reads at :61). Upstreams: Generate (realtime) https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta/models/{model}:generateContent; Stream generate .../:streamGenerateContent; Batch generate .../:batchGenerateContent; Cache (CRUD) https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta/cachedContents. Crucial distinction (W7B-DIRECT-VENDOR-PARITY): this is the AI Studio direct API (generativelanguage.googleapis.com), NOT the Vertex AI managed surface (aiplatform.googleapis.com). Per W7B 2026-06-29 Vertex-shift was abandoned; ship equivalent economic value (batch discount, prompt caching) on direct paths. See §7. Auth: API key as ?key=<API_KEY> query parameter (batch_gemini.py:223,243). Key env var: GEMINI_API_KEY per convention (LIVING:RESEARCH — confirm env var name parity vs cache_gemini.py:_api_key()).")

(chapter :number 6
         :title "§2.10–§2.12 — Firecrawl, Stripe, Web search routing"
         :section "2.10-2.12"
         :dialect "sakura"
         :audience "engineer"
         :training-eligible #f
         :confidentiality "internal"
         :provenance ((:source-path "/Users/alfred/code/sakura-scheme/docs/engineering/LACUNA-INTEGRATION-1.0.ENG.md") (:source-anchor "§2.10-§2.12"))
         :prose "Firecrawl (§2.10). Namespace web/* (web/scrape, web/search wired; web/extract, web/monitor, web/batch-scrape, web/map, web/agent, web/crawl, web/crawl-site, web/batch-status, web/monitor-create, web/map-urls, web/interact, web/extract-schema per scripts/audit_carts.py:29-34 V2_PENDING_VERBS — v2 surface awaiting wave-up). Plus firecrawl/policy-lookup for marketplace policy doc lookups. Modules: firecrawl/client.py (thin HTTP client; FIRECRAWL_BASE_URL='https://api.firecrawl.dev' at :42); firecrawl/tools.py (capability functions — scrape, search, extract, crawl, map); firecrawl/cache.py (local response cache); firecrawl/quota.py (daily-spend budget). Upstream: https://api.firecrawl.dev. Three endpoints currently exercised per client.py:4-13: web/scrape POST /v1/scrape; web/search POST /v1/search; web/extract POST /v1/extract (NOT wired in routes). Auth: API key resolution per client.py:13-29 — (1) FIRECRAWL_API_KEY env var (preferred); (2) ~/.curator/secrets/firecrawl.json with api_key key. If neither set, module does NOT raise — tools.py returns structured not_configured envelope so LLM can gracefully explain. Default search whitelist per client.py:46-58: DEFAULT_SEARCH_SITES constrains unsealed search tool to seller-handbook / community sites: Etsy seller handbook + community, eBay help + community + developer, Shopify help + community + dev, Meta business help + developers. Model can override with custom list. Policy doc roots: POLICY_DOC_ROOTS (client.py:62-84) bounds policy lookups to canonical policy pages per marketplace. Memory note: per MEMORY.md 'Firebase ALWAYS means Firecrawl' — voice-to-text slip.

Stripe (§2.11). Capability verbs: stripe/dashboard WIRED (link generator only — :1803 returns a deeplink, not an API call); stripe/payouts NOT WIRED — 17 carts blocked. No production API surface today for the API. Adding stripe/payouts would target POST https://api.stripe.com/v1/payouts plus GET /v1/payouts list. Per W7B Magic-tier override (CLAUDE.md 2026-06-23 directive) gating is academic for now — payment-on flip will make this operator-tier-gated again. Surface gap: 17 carts (light-purple / Dream tier) wait on stripe/payouts (1099-prep-annual, accountant-handoff-pack, bnpl-conversion-lift, cash-flow-forecast, chargeback-evidence-auto, chargeback-submit-auto, chargeback-win-rate, fee-reduce-optimize, gst-vat-handle, loan-readiness-check, payment-method-mix-opt, quarterly-est-tax-pay, runway-stress-test).

Web search routing (§2.12). Per CLAUDE.md 2026-06-14 W01 wire lock — web search routes through web/search + model/reasoner (L1) or on-device Sakura (L0). Perplexity, Pinterest, Reddit, Spotify were intentionally dropped. Today web/search is backed by firecrawl/tools.search (§2.10). client.py:46-58 default whitelist focuses search on seller-handbook + community + dev docs so operator's 'ask about Etsy policy' pattern returns canonical source, not a SERP of forum threads.")

(chapter :number 7
         :title "§2.13 — On-device speech-to-text (Parakeet TDT 0.6B v2)"
         :section "2.13"
         :dialect "sakura"
         :audience "engineer"
         :training-eligible #f
         :confidentiality "internal"
         :provenance ((:source-path "/Users/alfred/code/sakura-scheme/docs/engineering/LACUNA-INTEGRATION-1.0.ENG.md") (:source-anchor "§2.13"))
         :prose "Vendor-naming note: this subsection sits inside §2 (wire-call boundary), which per CLAUDE.md 2026-06-22 lock is the ONE place a vendor/model identifier may be written. 'Parakeet' and 'NVIDIA' appear here and nowhere else in the product; every other layer (Scheme, corpus, UI, TELEMETRY) uses the capability verb voice/transcribe. Do not copy the model string out of this subsection.

Status (honest, 2026-07-01). On-device model is a LOCKED design decision with a landed-but-unwired implementation module. Module exists and is complete; nothing imports it yet, so the live voice/transcribe route (verb_backings.py:2365) still delegates to voice/transcribe.py → Google Speech-to-Text (speech.googleapis.com/v1/speech:recognize, transcribe.py:30) or returns honest-null service-not-yet-wired (transcribe.py:106) when unconfigured. Parakeet module is the successor path; splicing it into the route is the remaining wiring task.

Design rationale (L0-STT lock, 2026-06-30). STT moves on-device: RTFx > 2000 (~40x Whisper baseline), model footprint ~600 MB, top-10 Open ASR leaderboard, zero-per-min cost, and the load-bearing property — audio never leaves the device, which is what makes the CIPA/BIPA/consent posture defensible. Capability generalizes past the voice-agent: every text field can carry a mic button because transcription cost is local and instant.

Module. curator-api/curator_api/voice/parakeet_stt.py (359 lines). _load_parakeet_model() at :29 loads nvidia/parakeet-tdt-0.6b-v2. Tries transformers first (:48); on ImportError/failure falls back to nemo_toolkit (:69-:78). Caches model + records _model_load_error on total failure (:84). _apply_phrase_boosting() at :93 is pure logit re-weighting: raises scores for tokens in hot_words (:115) so operator-specific vocabulary transcribes correctly. _transcribe_with_google_cloud() at :128 is fallback path only, gated by FALLBACK_STT=google (:240); uses speech.SpeechContext(phrases=hot_words, boost=20.0) at :153. transcribe_audio() at :214 is async entry point with hot_words param (:217). If local model is None AND FALLBACK_STT=google, delegates to cloud fallback (:240-:245); otherwise runs local model, applying phrase-boosting when hot_words present (:302-:304).

Fallback gating. Google cloud path is opt-in via env var only (FALLBACK_STT=google). Default deployment has no fallback: if on-device model fails to load and no fallback is configured, caller gets explicit error, not cloud round-trip it didn't consent to. Preserves 'audio never leaves the device' guarantee as default posture.

Health probe. routing/l1_manifest.py:132 _check_voice_transcribe() imports nemo.collections.asr (:135) to report readiness; registered under voice-transcribe capability key (:60, :174). Probe names the capability, not the vendor. Capability registry: verbs/system_capabilities.py:233 exposes audio/parakeet (STT), sibling to audio/aoede (TTS) at :226. LIVING:RESEARCH — system_capabilities.py:233 lists audio/parakeet with tier='L2'; L0-STT lock places on-device STT at L0. Correct the tier field, not the doc.

Phrase-boosting parity. Both local (_apply_phrase_boosting:93) and cloud (SpeechContext boost=20.0:153) paths honor same hot_words contract, so operator vocabulary transcribes identically regardless of backend. Matters for the 'mic button on every field' generalization: a field that knows its domain (e.g. a SKU field) can pass its known terms as hot_words.")

(chapter :number 8
         :title "§3 — OAuth + token model"
         :section "3"
         :dialect "sakura"
         :audience "engineer"
         :training-eligible #f
         :confidentiality "internal"
         :provenance ((:source-path "/Users/alfred/code/sakura-scheme/docs/engineering/LACUNA-INTEGRATION-1.0.ENG.md") (:source-anchor "§3"))
         :prose "Credential store. Per-operator OAuth tokens for marketplace vendors (Etsy, eBay, Shopify, Meta, Instagram, Google) live in curator-api/curator_api/vendors/credentials.py (CredentialStore). Store is encrypted at rest via Cortex crypto module (curator-api/curator_api/cortex/cortex_crypto.py); key derives from operator's session + per-machine HMAC key.

Service-account credentials. Cross-operator service-account keys (Google Cloud, Stripe, Firecrawl, Anthropic, Gemini API) live in ~/.curator-secrets/* with mode 0600 per CLAUDE.md 'Memory + secrets'. File paths follow env-var naming: ~/.curator-secrets/ANTHROPIC_API_KEY, ~/.curator-secrets/GEMINI_API_KEY, ~/.curator-secrets/FIRECRAWL_API_KEY, ~/.curator-secrets/CURATOR_CART_HMAC_KEY. (E1 redaction note: these are FILE-PATH names naming where a real key would live, not the key itself — safe to include.) Build script (scripts/build_cart_index.mjs:46-57, loadCartHmacKey) reads canonical file path as fallback when env var unset; per-vendor wire-call modules do the same.

OAuth flow per vendor. Etsy: OAuth 2.0 + PKCE, auth https://www.etsy.com/oauth/connect, token https://api.etsy.com/v3/public/oauth/token, scopes listings_r listings_w transactions_r email_r shops_r shops_w. eBay: OAuth 2.0 auth-code, auth https://auth.ebay.com/oauth2/authorize, token https://api.ebay.com/identity/v1/oauth2/token, scopes sell.inventory sell.marketing sell.account. Shopify: OAuth 2.0 shop-scoped, auth https://{shop}.myshopify.com/admin/oauth/authorize, token https://{shop}.myshopify.com/admin/oauth/access_token, scopes read_products write_products read_orders. Printify: OAuth 2.0, auth https://printify.com/oauth/authorize, token per vendors/registry.py:85-86. Meta: OAuth 2.0 + long-lived, auth https://www.facebook.com/v22.0/dialog/oauth, token https://graph.facebook.com/v22.0/oauth/access_token, scopes pages_manage_metadata catalog_management commerce_account_read_orders. Instagram: via Meta Business, scopes instagram_basic instagram_content_publish. Google: OAuth 2.0 + service-account, auth https://accounts.google.com/o/oauth2/v2/auth, token https://oauth2.googleapis.com/token, scopes vary per API. OAuth callbacks land at /api/oauth/<vendor>/callback (routes/oauth.py — LIVING:RESEARCH per-vendor callback paths to be confirmed).

Token refresh + rotation. Refresh tokens stored with access token. Wire-call modules detect 401 + refresh-on-need (lazy refresh — no background timer). On refresh failure, operator's credential marked stale; verb call returns service-not-yet-wired with reason <vendor>-token-expired. LIVING:RESEARCH — audit every store/<vendor>.py for 401-handling path; confirm refresh-on-need pattern is uniform vs ad-hoc.

HMAC chain for cart cost. Independent of vendor OAuth, cart corpus carries an HMAC over (slug, cost_tokens) per cart per PRICING-TOKEN-DESIGN-2026-06-18.md. Signer in curator-api/curator_api/signing.py; build script (scripts/build_cart_index.mjs:73-99) calls it as subprocess. Dispatcher verifies HMAC on every cart load; a tampered cost field fails verify and cart refuses to run. Integration-adjacent — the spine that keeps token budget honest across the verb-routing layer.")

(chapter :number 9
         :title "§4 — Rate limiting + back-pressure"
         :section "4"
         :dialect "sakura"
         :audience "engineer"
         :training-eligible #f
         :confidentiality "internal"
         :provenance ((:source-path "/Users/alfred/code/sakura-scheme/docs/engineering/LACUNA-INTEGRATION-1.0.ENG.md") (:source-anchor "§4"))
         :prose "Per-vendor rate limit philosophy. Every vendor has its own rate-limit shape (per-second token bucket, per-day quota, per-operator concurrency cap, per-app fair-share). Wire-call modules implement three layers: (1) Local token bucket — per-operator rate counter inside store client. (2) 429 + Retry-After honoring — every wire-call honors upstream 429 and returns rate-limited envelope with retry_after_s payload. Pattern visible in meta/dispatcher.py:73-76. (3) Daily-spend cap — for LLM vendors, cost ledger enforces per-tier daily cap per llm_router/cost_ledger.py:75-82: HARD_CAP_USD_PER_TIER = {free: 0.10, imagine: 1.00, dream: 10.00, magic: 100.00, default: 0.10}. Breach → cost-cap-exceeded. SRE override via CURATOR_COST_HARD_CAP_OVERRIDE_USD env (intended for testing).

Per-vendor specifics. Etsy v3: 10 q/s, 10,000/day per app — RateLimiter in stores/etsy.py. eBay: per-API per-token-type varies — RateLimiter in stores/ebay.py. Shopify: bucket-leak at 2 q/s (REST), GraphQL credits — RateLimiter in stores/shopify.py. Meta: BUC per operator — meta/dispatcher.py consults RateLimiter. Instagram: shared with Meta BUC. Printify: 600 req/minute per shop (LIVING:RESEARCH confirm). Anthropic: RPM/TPM per org (tier-scaled) — router + cost ledger. Gemini: RPM/RPD per project (tier-scaled) — router + cost ledger. Firecrawl: per-API-key quota per month — firecrawl/quota.py. Google APIs: per-project quota per API per day — google/quota.py.

Back-pressure envelope. Every rate-limited or quota-exceeded response uses canonical envelope: {ok: False, error: rate-limited or cost-cap-exceeded, reason: <vendor>-rate-limit or <vendor>-quota-exceeded, retry_after_s: <float> (advisory only)}. Cart escalates 'service-not-yet-wired (per SAKURA-SCHEME-1.0-SEALING.md §1.6) or branches into backoff state via (after retry_after_s 'retry ctx).")

(chapter :number 10
         :title "§5 — Error handling per vendor"
         :section "5"
         :dialect "sakura"
         :audience "engineer"
         :training-eligible #f
         :confidentiality "internal"
         :provenance ((:source-path "/Users/alfred/code/sakura-scheme/docs/engineering/LACUNA-INTEGRATION-1.0.ENG.md") (:source-anchor "§5"))
         :prose "Pattern is uniform across every wire-call module. Every exception class maps to a structured envelope; cart layer reads the envelope and escalates.

Error envelope canon. {ok: False, error: '<short-class>' (honest classification), reason: '<vendor>-<detail>' (capability-tagged)}. Recognized error classes per meta/dispatcher.py:62-82 + similar patterns: arg-shape (cart bug); operator-commit-required (write attempted without operator_commit); service-not-yet-wired (OAuth missing OR backing not shipped OR upstream unreachable); rate-limited (upstream 429 OR local bucket exhausted); cost-cap-exceeded (LLM cost ledger refused); upstream-rejected (upstream 4xx not in {429, 401}); upstream-error (upstream 5xx; transient); network-error (connection refused / DNS / TLS).

Per-vendor mapping. Etsy: etsy/client.py returns envelope directly. Auth fail = service-not-yet-wired (etsy-not-connected); 4xx = upstream-rejected; 5xx = upstream-error. eBay: same pattern. Shopify: same; GraphQL errors unwrapped — errors[].message becomes reason. Meta: meta/dispatcher.py:39-46 documents seven-step translation — input shape check → operator-commit check → BUC headroom check → MetaClient call → NotAuthorized → service-not-yet-wired, RateLimited → rate-limited, other upstream error → honest pass-through. Instagram: same as Meta. Anthropic: batch_anthropic.py honest-null on missing key; 4xx (other than 429) → upstream-rejected; 429 → rate-limited; 5xx → upstream-error. Cost-cap enforced at route layer (verb_backings.py:436-447). Gemini: same. Firecrawl: not-configured → not_configured (Firecrawl-specific shape from tools.py); cart-layer shim normalizes to service-not-yet-wired. Google: each google/*.py returns canonical envelope or delegates to standard Google API client which raises typed exceptions; wire-call shim catches and translates.

Honest-null discipline (cross-cutting). Per CLAUDE.md 'Honest nulls, no fluent-wrong' + sealed protocol §1.9 — every cart that receives null from a verb MUST escalate or branch explicitly. Silent-success a no-op is prohibited. Wire-call modules cooperate by returning the structured envelope; cart-side cooperates by inspecting ok before treating payload as data.")

(chapter :number 11
         :title "§6 — The 13 new Wave-4/5/6 route handlers + §6.6 world/knowledge"
         :section "6"
         :dialect "sakura"
         :audience "engineer"
         :training-eligible #f
         :confidentiality "internal"
         :provenance ((:source-path "/Users/alfred/code/sakura-scheme/docs/engineering/LACUNA-INTEGRATION-1.0.ENG.md") (:source-anchor "§6"))
         :prose "Per CART-WIREUP-AUDIT-2026-06-30.md and Wave-4/5/6, 13 routes were added to verb_backings.py on 2026-06-30, together unlocking ~131 previously INFRA-WAITING carts.

Voice (2 routes). voice/transcribe :2366 → voice.transcribe.transcribe(ctx) → Google Speech-to-Text (L1 tool call, not reasoning per CLAUDE.md L1/L2 definition). On-device Parakeet path (§2.13) is locked design successor but not yet spliced. voice/synthesize :2404 → voice.synth.synthesize(ctx) → Google TTS. Both require operator_commit: true (W6 task spec).

Mail (5 routes). mail/dispatch :2443 → mail.dispatcher.dispatch(ctx) (operator-commit required; upstream SMTP/SES). mail/template :2478 → mail.dispatcher.template(ctx) (pure render). mail/draft :2507 → mail.dispatcher.draft(ctx) (pure render). mail/with-gifs :2537 → mail.dispatcher.with_gifs(ctx) (pure render). mail/unsubscribe :2579 → mail.unsubscribe.honor_token/.mint_token (local signed-token store).

Notifications (1 route). notify/push :2634 → push.dispatcher.push(ctx) (W3C Web Push; operator-commit required).

Etsy orders/inventory/ledger/reprice (4 routes). etsy/orders :2678, etsy/inventory :2725, etsy/ledger :2770, etsy/reprice :2815 (last requires operator-commit).

Meta orders (1 route). meta/orders :2876 → meta.dispatcher.shop_orders.

Each route follows same scaffold: parse preamble, audit 'received', inject operator_commit, call backing, audit ok/module-error, return {trace_id, **result}. Pattern gives cost ledger + audit chain free observability.

§6.6 world/knowledge — catch-all research-and-learn route. Route: POST /api/verbs/world/knowledge (verbs/world_knowledge.py:117 world_knowledge_verb). Backs Scheme verb (world/knowledge :query X). Multi-upstream route: where a factual question the on-device 1.7B savant cannot answer gets escalated, answered, and — critically — written back so Sakura learns. Two backings for same verb: Scheme-runtime L0 stub (curator-web/src/scheme/base.js:425) returns honest-null escalator {kind: 'escalate', reason: 'service-not-yet-wired'}. Real answering happens in L1/L2 backend route. Four-step resolution: (1) Cache recall (:174 cortex_client.recall) — check operator's world-knowledge Cortex topic for prior answer keyed by slugify(query) at :72. Hit → return source='cache', no wire-call. (2) Workhorse (:209-:250 model_client.generate(tier='L1', capability='workhorse')) — self-hosted 8B answers from weights. Response parsed by parse_model_response (:81) into {answer, confidence}. (3) Escalate (:261-:317) — fires when time_sensitive OR confidence < confidence_threshold OR answer is None (:261-:265). Runs web_search_client.search(max_results=5) (:272), builds 3-source context (:281-:283), asks model_client.generate(tier='L2', capability='reasoner', temperature=0.2) (:302) to synthesize. source_tier='web_search+model_reasoner'. (4) Writeback (:350-:363 cortex_client.store(topic='world-knowledge', ...)) — persists {query, answer, confidence, source_tier, time_sensitive, retrieved_at} so next identical query short-circuits at Step 1. This is the learning loop. Vendor-naming: every module reference above uses capability tier (model_workhorse, model_reasoner, web_search) — no vendor identifier appears in world_knowledge.py. Upstream selection is router's job. Correct per CLAUDE.md 2026-06-22 lock. Honest-null discipline: two explicit escalate-returns guard failure paths — escalation-failed-with-no-prior-answer (:324-:332) and final-answer-still-None (:335-:343). Both return {kind:'escalate', reason:'service-not-yet-wired', verb:'world/knowledge'}. Cortex writeback failure (:364-:366) is logged but does NOT fail request — operator still gets answer; only learning side-effect skipped. Operator context: operator_id read from request middleware (:32-:33); missing operator id returns early rather than writing to null Cortex namespace.")

(chapter :number 12
         :title "§7 — Vertex-shift note (W7B-DIRECT-VENDOR-PARITY)"
         :section "7"
         :dialect "sakura"
         :audience "engineer"
         :training-eligible #f
         :confidentiality "internal"
         :provenance ((:source-path "/Users/alfred/code/sakura-scheme/docs/engineering/LACUNA-INTEGRATION-1.0.ENG.md") (:source-anchor "§7"))
         :prose "Original plan. Wave 7 (V1-V16) was originally scoped per WAVE-7-VERTEX-V1-V6-2026-06-29.md to migrate the LLM router through Google Vertex AI. Promise: consolidated invoicing, context-cache pricing, regional residency (EU/HIPAA), single managed surface for Anthropic + Gemini + future models.

The pivot. Per WAVE-7B-DIRECT-VENDOR-PARITY-2026-06-29.md:1-9 (architect directive 2026-06-29): 'Architect rescoped per the 2026-06-29 directive — Vertex's GCP setup overhead isn't worth our scale today. W7B wires the equivalent economic value on the DIRECT vendor paths instead.' Vertex AI module (google/vertex_ai.py) remains in tree for posterity; nothing in production routing calls it. Router lands every LLM call on direct vendor APIs (api.anthropic.com, generativelanguage.googleapis.com — specifically AI Studio, NOT Vertex).

What W7B delivered instead. Four new modules under llm_router/: batch_anthropic.py (50% off batch tier direct); batch_gemini.py (50% off batch tier direct — AI Studio, NOT Vertex); cache_gemini.py (75% off cached read after TTL direct); cost_ledger.py (per-vendor consolidated cost ledger — consolidated-invoice equivalent on direct-vendor path). Per WAVE-7B:60-67: batch_anthropic 29 tests; batch_gemini 27; cache_gemini 30; cost_ledger 26; total 112 (220/220 LLM tests pass).

The carts that 'wait on Vertex'. Per CART-VALIDATION-AUDIT-2026-06-29.md:1331 — 237 carts classified as WIRES-AFTER-VERTEX use model/deep-reasoning or model/workhorse on non-realtime cadence (weekly/monthly/quarterly/biweekly). They work today on direct vendor because both verbs have backing routes. 'Vertex shift' label was cost-reduction candidate, not correctness gate. W7B batch tier delivers same cost reduction on direct path; carts benefit without cart-side change.

EU residency / HIPAA. Features Vertex would have offered are NOT delivered by W7B. Remain open. Path forward when needed: route specific operator IDs to Vertex-managed deployment via router config, keeping direct path as default. LIVING:RESEARCH — document proposed dual-route fallback for the day EU residency becomes a customer ask.")

(chapter :number 13
         :title "§8 — W2-§4 namespace blocks (documents/analytics/ads resolutions)"
         :section "8"
         :dialect "sakura"
         :audience "engineer"
         :training-eligible #f
         :confidentiality "internal"
         :provenance ((:source-path "/Users/alfred/code/sakura-scheme/docs/engineering/LACUNA-INTEGRATION-1.0.ENG.md") (:source-anchor "§8"))
         :prose "Per CART-CANON-2026-06-30.md:1121,1219 — three verb-namespace blocks needed architect resolution before sealing. All three are resolved as of 2026-06-30.

documents/* resolution. Decision: documents/parse-invoice (W3) routes through Google Document AI per google/document_ai.py. Broader documents/parse verb (113 carts blocked per leverage table) lands in a future wave behind same module — Document AI's invoice processor is the floor. Rationale: Document AI is the only general-purpose document parsing API with structured output for invoice/receipt/W-2/form shapes. Status: documents/parse-invoice route exists at verb_backings.py:1286 but underlying google/document_ai.py module is partial — cart returns honest-null on most inputs. NOT WIRED; surfaced as service-not-yet-wired.

analytics/* resolution. Decision: analytics/report (W3) routes through GA4 via google/ga4_data.py. Broader analytics/ga4 namespace (2 carts blocked) lands in follow-up wave. Rationale: GA4 is operator's canonical analytics surface for their own store traffic. Report shape is opinionated (sessions/conversions/source-medium/event count) so cart layer can read it without per-operator schema chase. Status: route exists at verb_backings.py:1646; google/ga4_data.py module wired against GA4 Data API. LIVING:RESEARCH — confirm GA4 module pulls live data end-to-end with real GA4 property.

ads/* resolution. Decision: ads/insights (W3) routes through Google Ads via google/ads.py. Reuse operator's existing Google ad account credentials. Rationale: Google Ads insights are highest-leverage paid-ads signal for cart corpus (alternative — Meta Ads insights — goes through existing meta/* surface). Status: route exists at verb_backings.py:1779; google/ads.py is partial. NOT WIRED; surfaced as service-not-yet-wired.")

(chapter :number 14
         :title "§FC-ROUTES — Firecrawl-family expanded routes + capability→vendor mapping"
         :section "FC-ROUTES"
         :dialect "sakura"
         :audience "engineer"
         :training-eligible #f
         :confidentiality "internal"
         :provenance ((:source-path "/Users/alfred/code/sakura-scheme/docs/engineering/LACUNA-INTEGRATION-1.0.ENG.md") (:source-anchor "§FC-ROUTES"))
         :prose "The 2026-06-29 recovery-lane docs describe 9 web/* verbs Sakura now uses; each maps to a Firecrawl-family route. Vendor names appear nowhere; capability verbs only. The vendor firewall (lacuna-docs/canon/llm-naming-canon.md) hides the underlying provider.

Verb table with safety envelope. web/search — vendor-firewalled web search, returns URLs + snippets. K-anon/safety: per-op rate limit. documents/parse — parse a PDF/DOCX from URL or upload. Safety: sanitize on upload. web/extract-schema — LLM-guided schema extraction from URL. Safety: domain allowlist. web/monitor — subscription: watch URL, fire event on diff. Safety: per-op quota. web/crawl-site — bounded site crawl (max-pages cap). Safety: domain allowlist + max-pages required. web/agent — LLM-directed browsing (goal, not URL). Safety: domain allowlist + max-steps required + Priya audit. web/map-urls — return the URL-graph of a site. Safety: domain allowlist. web/interact — click/fill/submit on a page. Safety: domain allowlist + confirm-gate on writes. web/batch-scrape — parallel scrape of URL list. Safety: per-op quota.

Full use-case survey is in the recovery-lane FIRECRAWL-* docs; they move to _archive-2026-07-11/lacuna-integration/ during archive pass.

Capability → vendor mapping for the 9 new verbs. Marcus + Priya locked the vendor mapping 2026-06-29; the LLM-naming canon (llm-naming-canon.md) is the reference. Every crossing carries the Priya audit note 'domain allowlist enforced at verb-registration time' per SAKURA-AUTOMATIONS-1.0.ENG.md §E2 audit.")

(chapter :number 15
         :title "§SLAT — Cross-system messages on the SLAT wire"
         :section "SLAT"
         :dialect "sakura"
         :audience "engineer"
         :training-eligible #f
         :confidentiality "internal"
         :provenance ((:source-path "/Users/alfred/code/sakura-scheme/docs/engineering/LACUNA-INTEGRATION-1.0.ENG.md") (:source-anchor "§SLAT"))
         :prose "Cross-refs: SLAT-1.0.SPEC.md, LOAM-1.0.ENG.md §SLAT, CORTEX-1.0.ENG.md §SLAT, SECURITY-CANONICAL-1.0.ENG.md §SLAT. Task #62 landed the ENG-tree surface pass; this section threads SLAT through the integration contract, wire-call envelopes, OAuth capability tokens, rate-limit envelopes, and error envelopes. Additive to §0-§7; no deletes.

Doctrine. Integration is the discipline of speaking to systems Lacuna does not own. The vendor speaks its own protocol; the vendor-firewall (§0.2) translates that into Lacuna's capability verbs; the capability verbs consume and produce SLAT records. Every message crossing the integration seam is a slat. Load-bearing property: cross-system messages have the same shape as intra-system messages. Foreman-to-worker (intra-Lacuna) is a message slat. Sakura-to-Etsy (extra-Lacuna, through the vendor-firewall) is a message slat whose :to field names the capability verb, whose :detail is the vendor-neutral operation, and whose signed envelope carries the OAuth capability that authorizes the call.

Mailbox envelopes are .slatl. Worker mailboxes live at ~/.lacuna/mailboxes/<name>.slatl (SLAT §5.8 migration path). One message per line. Producers append; consumers tail. Every line is a message slat. Example: (message :v 1 :from 'foreman :to 'worker/mlx-1 :ts inst :detail (start-training-run :seed 4137 :adapters ... :max-iter 68520)). Malformed lines produce _bad-line sentinels (SLAT §5.3 tolerant mode) — mailbox never blocks on parse failure. Backward compat: mailboxes accept JSON lines during migration window. Reader tries SLAT first, JSON second, emits deprecation warning on JSON path.

Vendor wire-call envelopes are record slats. §2 walks per-vendor modules. Each hides vendor API behind capability verb. Wire-call responses fit record slat shape: (record :kind 'etsy-listing-response :listing-id ... :title ... :price-cents 3400M :currency USD :quantity 3 :updated-at inst). Vendor's raw JSON never crosses firewall in that shape — wire-call shim reads vendor JSON and emits canonical slat record. Downstream (cart code, Cortex writes, telemetry) sees slat, not vendor JSON. Vendor swaps become adapter changes. Money fields use bigdecimal (M-suffix per SLAT §3.3) because money is not a vector.

OAuth + capability envelopes. §3 describes OAuth model. Every wire call carries capability token; token is a signed slat (SLAT §6.5): (capability :grants (:read 'etsy/listings/*' :write 'etsy/listings/1234567890') :subject 'operator/op-042' :issuer 'lacuna-vendor-firewall' :vendor 'etsy :not-before inst :not-after inst :nonce b64). Wrapped in (signed :body <capability> :signature <ed25519> ...). Vendor-firewall verifies signature, checks :vendor, matches :grants against call, then translates to vendor's OAuth headers. Rogue calls fail signature verification before any vendor API is touched. HMAC chain for cart cost (§3.5) uses same signed-slat pattern; chain of envelopes is a Merkle tree per SLAT §6.7.

Rate-limit + back-pressure envelopes. When vendor-firewall throttles, response envelope carries record slat with rate-limit context: (record :kind 'rate-limit-hit :vendor 'etsy :verb 'etsy/listing-update :remaining 0 :reset-at inst :backoff-ms 8000 :suggestion 'defer-and-retry). Consumers pattern-match on :kind rate-limit-hit and enter back-pressure envelope path (§4.3). Deferred work uses SLAT §3.8 reserved #_pending tag.

Error envelopes use reserved #_error tag. Every vendor error crosses firewall as slat with reserved #_error tag: #_error (error :vendor 'etsy :verb 'etsy/listing-update :code 403 :vendor-code 'OAUTH_INVALID_SCOPE :capability-canon 'insufficient-scope :recoverable #f :ts inst). Reserved-tag shape means downstream consumers can distinguish real record from error record with one lexical check. #_error is one of four reserved diagnostic tags. :capability-canon normalizes vendor's error code to Lacuna capability-error taxonomy; vendor-specific :vendor-code stays available for audit but downstream logic uses canonical form.

Cross-refs. SLAT primitives — SLAT-1.0.SPEC.md §3. Mailbox migration to .slatl — SLAT §5.8. Signing envelope — SLAT §6.2. Capability tokens — SLAT §6.5. Reserved tags — SLAT §3.8. Merkle attestation — SLAT §6.7. Loam ingest of integration events — LOAM-1.0.ENG.md §SLAT. SECURITY-CANONICAL — signed envelopes + capability posture. TELEMETRY-MEDIAN §SLAT — cost row schema uses the record slat form.")

(references
